bio.experienceSummary:
As a nurturing and responsible individual with three years of experience in childcare, I am thrilled to introduce myself as a reliable childcare provider. My passion for caring for children stems from my genuine desire to foster their growth and development. I believe that every child deserves a safe and nurturing environment in which to thrive.

My calm and patient demeanor, coupled with my friendly and approachable nature, allows me to connect with children effortlessly. I prioritize open communication with parents, providing regular updates about their child's day and promptly addressing any concerns that may arise.

With a COLLEGE DEGREE and certifications in both First Aid Training and CPR Training, I am well-equipped to handle any situation that may arise. I am comfortable caring for up to three children of varying ages, from infants to preteens. My diverse skill set includes cooking and meal preparation, light housekeeping, and swimming supervision.

Hi, I am a full-time marketing professional in Manhattan. While marketing is my career, I love spending time with kids.

- I worked as a children's birthday party hostess for 3 years.
- I was an Au Pair in Spain for a summer for a family with kids aged 5, 9, and 11.
- I started and coached a middle school track and cross country team while in college.
- I was a babysitter / nanny in Jackson Hole, WY for a summer.

I believe in empathetic communication with children as they learn to navigate their personalities, emotions, and relationships. I also believe in adapting to their caregivers' parenting styles.

When babysitting, I like to play games, go to the park, and/or even do some baking. I like to have fun, too!

Feel free to ask me any questions. I'd love to step in to help.

Looking for full time role starting April 5th - early July 


I've spent over a decade working closely with children, both as a nanny and a teacher, and it's truly where my heart lies. As a nanny, I've specialized in caring for newborns, creating a safe and loving environment for their earliest moments. As a teacher, I've had the privilege of inspiring young minds and helping them grow with patience and encouragement. On top of that, I manage a nonprofit dedicated to supporting disabled children with the education and emotional care they deserve. Helping kids thrive, no matter their background or abilities, is what drives me every single day

description.originalText: Jade used to babysit me when I was younger and she is the best! She comes up with fun activities and is very attentive. She always made sure my siblings and I had the best time while she was at ours, making up new games for us to play and taking us outside. 10/10 recommend!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi! I have been babysitting for the past 16 years. I am local to Tribeca (10013) and a native New Yorker. 

I love children and am great with all ages. I have a specialty in special needs as I have two nephews that are autistic. I am looking forward to meeting you! Feel free to ask me any specific questions.

description.displayText: We were unable to use Erin because our kids weren't feeling well when we booked her. However, she was very easy to contact and wonderful with her follow up. I would definitely try to get in touch with her again.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi, I'm Liz! I've spent the past 9 years working with kids, and it's something I truly enjoy. I started in high school with early childhood education courses, earning my DCF 40-hour certification. Since then, I've worked with children of all ages through daycare, tutoring, and three years of nannying during college. Now living in New York and working full-time in advertising, I'd love to find a part-time or weekend babysitting job to keep doing what I love!

description.displayText: Liz is a very responsible and caring girl. Over the years, having worked together or for similar people, I know she is capable of caring for any child. She is excellent with children of all ages and has a great work ethic. Any family would be making the smart choice, by choosing Liz.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello, my name is Fiona. I am a European nanny with over 25 years of professional nanny experience in New York City, both in short and long-term positions . 
I am a warm and loving nanny who is enthusiastic, reliable, and resourceful. Attentive with a genuine love for children and their well-being . Currently, I am seeking a long-term role with the right family, but am open to jobs with shorter time commitments.

description.displayText: Fiona came into our lives when it was time to return to work from maternity leave as a first time mom. She made what was a stressful and emotional time into the smoothest transition possible. Fiona is very responsible, dependable and so loving and kind to our now 13 month old daughter. She was super helpful during times like teething and starting solids. If we ever ran late from work we never had to worry. Fiona truly loves what she does and it certainly shows. Seeing how excited our daughter gets when she walks through the door in the mornings is the best review we could get. Highly recommend Fiona!!!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello! I have nannied many families over the past few years as well as built my career in a mental health and child development focus. I have experience with ages infant through teenagers, as well as career experience within hospitals including the NICU and other health care settings. I love to support in any child's learning and growing into themselves and personality. Personally, I love all things centered around art and creativity so I would be thrilled to share that passion while nannying! Please let me know with any questions, I look forward to hearing from you soon. 

I'd describe my personality as patient, inquisitive, and gentle.

Hi, I have cared for children my entire adulthood, 19+ years now. I love what I do for a living and hope to stay in this type of work for a very long time. I have cared for several newborns, infants and a couple sets of multiples throughout my years of experience. I have held some of my positions for years at a time. I have traveled to different countries with families I have worked with in the past and they continue to be in my life today. I am a New York transplant from California, I've been here 6 years and absolutely love it. I am very fortunate to have incredible references. I have a strong work ethic as this is the way I support myself and sustain my lifestyle. Hopefully I can be of help to you and your family!

I love working with kids and have been babysitting since age 12. I am patient, playful, and kind. I have worked in homes, schools and therapeutic environments with children of diverse needs. I have also nannied and been a special needs caregiver for many years. I have a lot of experience with adhd and Autism. I am passionate about this work. I am also a certified neurodiverse children's yoga instructor and offering lessons. I am currently studying for higher certifications and looking for part-time and occasional opportunities. Thanks for your time!

description.displayText: Kellinann spent an afternoon with our special needs daughter and was just lovely - calm, competent, and ready to play. I would absolutely hire her again.
description.originalText: Kellinann spent an afternoon with our special needs daughter and was just lovely - calm, competent, and ready to play. I would absolutely hire her again.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello families!! My name is Fayza!
I have degree in Early Childhood Education in one of the best universities of South America. I've spend 5 years studying about education and your many theories. I work based on the Constructivism and I like working with Montessori and Waldorf as well. This way you can count on me for more than just basic care and playing with your child. You may have expectations of someone who will working on your baby's motor and intellectual development. Besides that, I've studied theater and dance. I love to involve art during my daily work routine.
*11 years of experience with different ages: I worked as a teacher assistant with ages of 1 month to 11 years old and kindergarten teacher during 7 years in Brazil. Then I moved to the US in 2018, and I've been working as a nanny ever since. I'm responsible, trustworthy, affectionate, patient, dedicated flexible and easygoing.

I can't wait to hear from you!

description.displayText: Faiza is an excellent nanny! She has many years of experience, she's loving, caring, do many educational activities with the kids, and cooks really well!! Your kid(s) are going to be on incredible hands!
